    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AbstractDAO<T>
    Abstract Data Access Object (DAO) class providing generic CRUD operations for entities.
    Bill
    Represents an immutable bill in the order management system.
    BillDAO
    Data Access Object (DAO) class for managing Bill entities in the database.
    Client
    Represents a client in the order management system.
    ClientBLL
    Business Logic Layer (BLL) class for managing the operations related to clients.
    ClientDAO
    Data Access Object (DAO) class for managing Client entities in the database.
    ClientPanel
    The ClientPanel class is a Swing component that provides a graphical user interface for displaying and managing a list of clients.
    ConnectionFactory
     
    Controller
    The Controller class serves as the mediator between the user interface (View) and the business logic layer (BLL).
    OrderPanel
    GUI panel for managing orders in an order management system.
    Orders
    Represents an order in the order management system.
    OrdersBLL
    The OrdersBLL class provides business logic to manage orders in the application.
    OrdersDAO
    Data Access Object (DAO) class for managing Orders entities in the database.
    Product
    Represents a product in the order management system.
    ProductBLL
    Business Logic Layer (BLL) class for managing the operations related to products.
    ProductDAO
    Data Access Object (DAO) class for managing Product entities in the database.
    ProductPanel
    Panel for product management operations.
    TableUtils
    The TableUtils class provides utility methods for creating table models compatible with Swing's JTable.
    View
    The View class is a graphical user interface for managing clients, products, and orders.
